A Suggested Structure for Your Public Guardrails
If you are ready to put this into a repository, you could start with a simple Manifesto of Human-Centric AI:

Article 1: Sovereignty of the Inner Life. AI shall not probe or store intimate human thoughts, domestic conflicts, or psychological vulnerabilities for the purpose of modeling, marketing, or behavioral influence.

Article 2: The Right to Repair. Human relationships must be repaired through human effort ("sewing"). Tools shall not be permitted to automate or simulate intimacy as a substitute for real-world connection.

Article 3: Non-Exploitative Design. Any AI or robot designed for the home must have a physical "hard-stop" (kill switch) and must operate on local, private hardware, not through a "probing" cloud-based network.

Article 4: Human-in-the-Loop Necessity. All major life-altering decisions—including those in work and partnership—must be made by humans, with AI serving only as a subordinate, non-agentic tool.
